# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the MySmile React + Vite application following the latest official documentation from Vercel.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Package**: `@vercel/speed-insights` (version added to package.json)
- **Method**: Installed using npm (project uses Bun as package manager per package.json, but npm was used in sandbox environment)
- **Status**: ✅ Successfully installed

### 2. Code Changes
**Modified File**: `MySmile/src/App.tsx`

**Changes**:
1. Added import statement at the top of the file:
   ```typescript
   import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/react";
   ```

2. Added the `<SpeedInsights />` component within the Router component, placed at the root level of the app to track all pages:
   ```typescript
   <div className="min-h-screen bg-white font-sans text-stone-900 selection:bg-stone-100 selection:text-stone-900 flex flex-col">
     <SpeedInsights />
     <Toaster position="top-right" richColors />
     <Navbar />
     ...
   </div>
   ```

### 3. Updated Files
- `MySmile/package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `MySmile/package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency tree
- `MySmile/src/App.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights component

## Implementation Details

### Framework Detection
- **Framework**: React 19.1.2 with Vite 7.0.0
- **Router**: React Router DOM v7.13.1
- **Package Manager**: Bun 1.2.22 (as specified in package.json)

### Integration Approach
Following the official Vercel documentation, the SpeedInsights component was:
1. Imported from `@vercel/speed-insights/react` (React-specific package)
2. Placed at the root level of the application (inside the Router, at the top of the main div)
3. No additional configuration required - the component auto-initializes

### Placement Rationale
The SpeedInsights component was placed:
- Inside the `<Router>` component to ensure it has access to routing context
- At the top of the main application div, before other components
- This ensures it tracks all page navigations and performance metrics across the entire application

